menu_buildjob_lever
[TITLE]The Manual: Lever Menu[/TITLE]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]How to Get Here[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_BUILDJOB] from the main view and move to a lever (or pressure plate).
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Description[C:7:0:0]
[B]
The lever menu is a standard menu, but the tasks are unusual.  The lever (or pressure plate) can be linked to one or
more buildings.  Pulling the lever (or stepping on the pressure plate) causes the effect to be trigger.  Linking a
building requires two mechanisms and takes some time.
[B]
The effects are as follows:
[B]
[C:3:0:1]Bridge[C:7:0:0] Raise/lower[R]
[C:3:0:1]Cage/Chain[C:7:0:0] Release occupants[R]
[C:3:0:1]Door/Hatch[C:7:0:0] Open/close (otherwise unuseable)[R]
[C:3:0:1]Floodgate/Grate/Bars[C:7:0:0] Open/close[R]
[C:3:0:1]Support[C:7:0:0] Collapses[R]
[C:3:0:1]Spears/Spikes[C:7:0:0] Retract/extend[R]
[C:3:0:1]Gear assembly[C:7:0:0] Engage/Disengage[R]
